message.content: cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.CR, cs.LO. The paper deals with dynamic distributed storage algorithms and their liveness properties, which are central topics in distributed computing. The paper also discusses failure detectors, which are commonly used in distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also touches on topics related to cryptography and security (cs.CR), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), but to a lesser extent.
